<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.001H87/34.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Huerta, after arrest to-day on second complaint, failed to give $15,000
                            bond, which he could have, easily given, and has been sent to county
                            jail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>